HEADWORD: mandil
<hw>man"dil</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧n"d⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>mandil</ets>; cf. Sp. & Pg. <ets>mandil</ets> a coarse apron, a
haircloth; all from Ar. <ets>mandil</ets> tablecloth, handkerchief,
mantle, fr. LGr. <grk>mandh`lion</grk>, fr. L. <ets>mantile</ets>,
<ets>mantele</ets>. See <er>Mantle</er>.]</ety> <def>A loose outer
garment worn the 16th and 17th centuries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

